# Slatepress design system (slatepress-site repo)

This rule encodes the canonical brand tokens for **slatepress.co** specifically. Each SlatePress vertical-brand repo has its own `:root` block with its own tokens; this rule is repo-scoped and applies only to slatepress-site edits.

The source of truth for these tokens is the `:root` block at the top of `index.html`. If they ever drift, this rule should be updated to match - the live file wins.

## Canonical tokens

```css
:root {
  /* Backgrounds */
  --bg:         #FFFFFF;   /* page canvas - pure white */
  --bg-soft:    #FAFAFA;   /* secondary surface */
  --bg-card:    #F7F7F5;   /* card surfaces, subtle warm tint */

  /* Text */
  --ink:        #1C1B1F;   /* primary text, near-black with subtle warm undertone */
  --ink-soft:   #5C5C66;   /* secondary text */
  --slate:      #85858C;   /* tertiary text */
  --slate-light:#9CA3AF;   /* quaternary muted text */

  /* Borders / rules */
  --rule:       #E8E8E8;   /* default 1px borders, dividers */
  --rule-soft:  #F0F0F0;   /* subtle dividers */
  --rule-strong:#1C1B1F;   /* emphasized borders (matches --ink) */

  /* Brand accent */
  --blue:       #2563EB;   /* PRIMARY BRAND BLUE - logo "/" + primary CTAs */
  --blue-deep:  #1D4ED8;   /* hover state for blue */
  --blue-soft:  #EFF6FF;   /* light blue tint for backgrounds/badges */

  /* Semantic */
  --emerald:    #059669;   /* success / live-status (the "DIGITAL MARKETING DISTRIBUTION PARTNER" green dot) */

  /* Layout */
  --max:        1080px;    /* content max-width */
}
```

## Type stack

**Inter only.** Single sans-serif throughout. No display serif, no monospace by default. If a special case requires another face, raise the question before adding.

```css
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
```

## Cardinal rules for slatepress-site

- **Pure white canvas (`--bg`).** Backgrounds step down to `--bg-soft` for alternating sections and `--bg-card` for cards. Off-white or cream backgrounds are wrong for this site.
- **Brand blue (`--blue` #2563EB) is the one accent.** It appears on the logo's `/`, primary CTAs, `::selection`, focus rings, and at most one emphasis moment per viewport. No second accent. The emerald is reserved for live-status indicators only (e.g., the eyebrow's pulsing dot), not as a decorative color.
- **No new hex codes.** If a component needs a color not in the `:root` block, raise it as a design-system question before adding. Drift across pages is the failure mode.
- **No gradient buttons, no carousels, no Lorem ipsum, no emoji in production UI.**
- **High contrast.** Body text against `--bg` should hit WCAG AAA (7:1 ratio). `--slate-light` (#9CA3AF) is borderline on white - use only for non-essential tertiary text.

## When designing or reviewing UI in this repo

Defer to the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill (installed globally at `~/.claude/skills/premium-web-designer/`). It encodes the universal taste rules and the workflow for loading brand tokens. This rule supplies the brand-specific tokens it will load for slatepress-site.

When `premium-web-designer` fires, it should:
1. Ask "What are we designing today?"
2. On the answer "slatepress.co" or any slatepress-site edit, load the tokens above.
3. Apply universal taste principles on top.
4. Produce code that references the brand's variable names (`--blue`, `--ink`, `--bg-card`) directly - never invent token names.
